    <text id="A6500T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Joseph Pillsberry writes Lorenzo Sibert to relieve him from an office he has
                    held, and thanks him for kind treatment of his daughter.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Lorenzo Sibert Esqr.</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1856-08-07"><del rend="none" hand="h1"/> Aug 7th /56</date>
                        <name type="place">Mount Pleasant <del rend="none" hand="h1"/></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your resignation of June 24<hi rend="super">th</hi>, was received, on the second
                    day of the present month, and is accepted, and in consideration of the faithful,
                    and Gentlemanlike manner in which you have filled the Office you have so long
                    held, you are hereby honorably discharged from the office of <unclear>Father</unclear>
                    <unclear>
                        <hi rend="underline">protem</hi>
                    </unclear>, to M. L. Pillsberry, by the real <unclear>Father</unclear> Joseph
                    Pillsberry.</p>

                <p>I wish herein to tender you &amp; your good Wife, &amp; all other
                    Gentlemen and Ladies in Virginia my sincere gratitude for the many tokens of
                    Kindness, and respect shown to my Daughter, while she was among you, and it is
                    my earnest desire that no evils, but much good may arise from her stay, and
                    labours in your vicinity.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours truly</salute>
                    <signed>Jospeh Pillsberry</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">on his 57<hi rend="super">th birth day</hi></seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
